  "summary": "Casdoor allows users to bypass configured MFA requirements",
  "details": "Casdoor versions 2.362.0 and earlier contain a logic flaw in the social‑login binding flow that allows users to bypass configured MFA requirements. The binding‑rule code path in controllers/auth.go calls HandleLoggedIn directly without invoking checkMfaEnable. Any user authenticating via this path is logged in without MFA enforcement.",
